    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-05-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-05-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="618"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d618">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 337.11/485</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Griffith</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 6, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Consular agent Guantanamo reports burning and sacking Olimpo, Palmarejo and
                    Belona. Yesterday buildings Citero iron mines known Nimanima, Government chart,
                    burned. Government forces fled. <hi rend="italic">Machias</hi> left breaking
                    communication with naval station. Captain marines reports two thousand armed
                    rebels near Daiquiri. Mining properties and wharf here inadequately protected,
                    need war vessel and five hundred additional marines immediately. Very
                    urgent.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Griffith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
